ox:Luc) line is an excellent tool for studying the regulation of the circadian clock and its maturation in vivo and in real-time. Furthermore, it is highly suitable for in vivo screens targeting the core clock mechanism that take into account the complexity of an intact organism. Finally, it allows mapping of clock activity in the brain of a vertebrate model organism with prominent adult neurogenesis and high regeneration capacity.},
